<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12139d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12139d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12139d"> 139(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ kill victim to save king <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12139d"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Evidently the Heliopolitans had argued that the blood of a victim would rejuvenate the king, that the king need not be killed when he became old, and thereby had placed the kingship on an entirely different footing. Henceforth the king had power over his subjects, and was no longer forced to sacrifice himself for the good of the community. It is from this episode that many of the troubles of mankind possibly take their origin. For, from the practice of offering slaves as human sacrifices instead of the king, the custom of warfare evidently developed <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 39-40</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Possibly crossed out in place of <a name="n12139b" href="n12all.htm#n12139b">N12 (VI.B.14):139(b)</a> above. </mm> </dd></dl>
